<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-28T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-28T15:00:00-05:00" n="157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">794A.011/7–2351: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Republic of China</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-28T16:00:00-04:00">July 28,
                                    1951—4 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>74. Ur 105 Jul 23. Dept approves ur reply to <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> and considers this reply adequate.</p>
                        <p>Established US policy is to deny Formosa to Commie China and Seventh
                            Fleet assigned mission preventing Commie attack on island. However,
                            difference of view among concerned countries re polit status Formosa and
                            Natl Govt and fact Natl Govt’s objectives go beyond defense Formosa and
                            embrace reconquest mainland China cause special problems re Formosa
                            which make unlikely its inclusion under existing circumstances in any
                            gen collective security system which may develop in the Far East.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>